<div itemprop="articleBody">
<h3>Tutorial 4. Sewing In the Zipper.</h3>
<p></p>
<p><strong>I put the ribbon over the zipper that I have previously opened and sew it on moving along the edge with the one-sided zipper presser foot. </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image002.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image004.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image006.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image008.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>And I sew down the other side of the zipper tape, too.</strong> Then I swap the one-sided foot for the invisible zipper presser foot and put the mesh face side up. </p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image010.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I place the zipper on the mesh, align it with the edge of the cut, place it all under the presser foot and start sewing.</strong> Beware not to stretch out the mesh! </p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image012.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image014.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image016.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image018.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I close the sewn-on zipper. </strong>It looks very pretty: instead of zipper teeth you can see a strap of nude colour overlaid by a decorative white ribbon. </p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image020.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I will sew button pearls onto the ribbon</strong> - they are perfect for this particular dress.</p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image022.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I switch back to the regular presser foot and sew down the central seam below the zipper. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image024.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></strong></p>
<p><strong>You can finish the central seam with a special bias tape for nylon edges</strong> to give it a cleaner look. I won't do that on our training sample. </p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image026.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding6/Tutorial%204_files/image028.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>

</div> <!-- Itemprop END: articleBody -->
